assets.description: Up the street from my house there is a private drive with a sign out front that says Camp Huntington. It’s somewhat of a mysterious street, with a house near the entrance with a couple roosters – an unusual sight and sound in Los Angeles. If you pull up the drive a little bit you find this dilapitated log cabin. I suspect it must have some historical significance, otherwise why would it still be left standing, perhaps this was property once owned by Mr Huntington himself. Who knows. I captured this using the new LiDAR iPad using the Polycam app. Learn more at: https://polycam.ai/

assets.description:
#galacticsafari
H'tEph The Sun Eater.
Worshipped by humankind during the time of the pharaohs as the "scarab" who pushed the sun across the skies, H'tEph is actually a Klaavalian Dune Bug, the adult form of the Klaavalian Dune Larvae, having undergone metamorphosis. H'tEph The Sun Eater is unique in the metaverse for being able to directly draw energy from stars by wrapping its supernova sized mass around smaller suns. This rarely captured behavior has only been observed among the female of the species and scientists assume it has something to do with the birthing cycle, more data is required...
